{"format":"tiptap/v1","updatedAt":"2026-06-22T04:25:22.292Z","doc":{"type":"doc","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Unsupervised learning"},{"type":"text","text":" is a type of machine learning where the algorithm learns patterns from "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"unlabeled data"},{"type":"text","text":"—data with no explicit correct answers or labels provided."}]},{"type":"blockquote","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Simple definition:"},{"type":"text","text":" “Unsupervised learning is when a computer explores the data on its own to find hidden patterns and structures, "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"without being told what to look for"},{"type":"text","text":".”"}]}]},{"type":"horizontalRule"},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":2},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Core idea: learning from patterns without labels"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"In unsupervised learning:"}]},{"type":"bulletList","content":[{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"You give the model "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"only input data"},{"type":"text","text":" (no labels)"}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"The model discovers "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"hidden structures"},{"type":"text","text":", groupings, or patterns automatically"}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"There is often "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"no single “right” answer"},{"type":"text","text":"—the goal is to find interesting or useful structure"}]}]}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Example (cats vs. dogs):"}]},{"type":"bulletList","content":[{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Supervised"},{"type":"text","text":": You give labeled images: “cat”, “dog” and teach the model to recognize them."}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Unsupervised"},{"type":"text","text":": You give a bunch of cat and dog images "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"italic"}],"text":"without labels"},{"type":"text","text":"; the model figures out on its own that some images look similar (cats) and others look similar (dogs), forming clusters without knowing the names."}]}]}]},{"type":"horizontalRule"},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":2},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Unsupervised learning in Classical Machine Learning"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"In classical machine learning, unsupervised learning is used mainly for:"}]},{"type":"orderedList","attrs":{"start":1,"type":null},"content":[{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Clustering"},{"type":"text","text":" – grouping similar data points:"}]}]}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"- K-Means clustering - Hierarchical clustering - DBSCAN - Example: group customers by purchasing behavior, group products by similarity"}]},{"type":"orderedList","attrs":{"start":1,"type":null},"content":[{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Dimensionality Reduction"},{"type":"text","text":" – simplifying data while preserving structure:"}]}]}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"- PCA (Principal Component Analysis) - t-SNE - Autoencoders (in some contexts) - Example: reduce 100 features to 10 principal components for visualization or faster models"}]},{"type":"orderedList","attrs":{"start":1,"type":null},"content":[{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Other pattern discovery"},{"type":"text","text":":"}]}]}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"- Density estimation - Association rule learning - Anomaly detection (sometimes)"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"These are all "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"discriminative or exploratory"},{"type":"text","text":" methods in classical ML that don’t rely on labels."}]},{"type":"horizontalRule"},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":2},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Unsupervised learning in Generative AI"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Generative AI"},{"type":"text","text":" heavily relies on "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"unsupervised"},{"type":"text","text":" and "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"self-supervised"},{"type":"text","text":" learning:"}]},{"type":"bulletList","content":[{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Unsupervised generative models"},{"type":"text","text":":"}]}]}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"- "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"GANs"},{"type":"text","text":" (Generative Adversarial Networks): learn to generate realistic images without labels - "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Diffusion models"},{"type":"text","text":": learn to generate images, audio, etc. from noise, without explicit labels - "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"VAEs"},{"type":"text","text":" (Variational Autoencoders): learn a latent representation and generate data"}]},{"type":"bulletList","content":[{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Self-supervised generative models"},{"type":"text","text":" (a form of unsupervised learning):"}]}]}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"- "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"LLMs"},{"type":"text","text":" (e.g., GPT, ChatGPT): predict the next token in a sequence - Labels are "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"derived from the data itself"},{"type":"text","text":" (e.g., next word), not manually provided"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Key difference:"}]},{"type":"bulletList","content":[{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Classical unsupervised ML"},{"type":"text","text":":"}]}]}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"- Focuses on "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"clustering"},{"type":"text","text":", "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"dimensionality reduction"},{"type":"text","text":", and "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"pattern discovery"},{"type":"text","text":" - Often used for "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"analysis"},{"type":"text","text":" and "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"exploration"},{"type":"text","text":" of data"}]},{"type":"bulletList","content":[{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Generative AI (unsupervised/self-supervised)"},{"type":"text","text":":"}]}]}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"- Focuses on "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"learning the full data distribution"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"inlineMath","attrs":{"latex":"P(\\text{data})"}},{"type":"text","text":" - Then "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"generating new content"},{"type":"text","text":" (text, images, code) by sampling from that distribution"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"So unsupervised learning is a "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"bridge"},{"type":"text","text":":\n- In classical ML, it’s used for "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"exploration and structure discovery"},{"type":"text","text":".\n- In generative AI, it’s used for "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"learning how data looks overall"},{"type":"text","text":" and then "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"creating new data"},{"type":"text","text":"."}]},{"type":"horizontalRule"},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":2},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Supervised vs. Unsupervised (core difference)"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"The key distinction is how the "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"objective function"},{"type":"text","text":" works:"}]},{"type":"bulletList","content":[{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Supervised learning"},{"type":"text","text":":"}]}]}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"- You have "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"labels"},{"type":"text","text":" for each training example - The objective function compares the model’s prediction to the "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"true label"},{"type":"text","text":" - Used when there is a clear correct answer (classification, regression)"}]},{"type":"bulletList","content":[{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Unsupervised learning"},{"type":"text","text":":"}]}]}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"- You "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"do not have labels"},{"type":"text","text":"; there may be no single “right” answer - The objective function judges how good or plausible the model’s output is (e.g., “does this image look realistic?”, “are points in this cluster similar?”) - Used for clustering, dimensionality reduction, and generative modeling"}]},{"type":"horizontalRule"},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":2},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Key takeaways"}]},{"type":"bulletList","content":[{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Unsupervised learning"},{"type":"text","text":" learns patterns from "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"unlabeled data"},{"type":"text","text":", discovering hidden structures without explicit instructions."}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"In "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"classical ML"},{"type":"text","text":", it’s mainly used for "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"clustering"},{"type":"text","text":", "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"dimensionality reduction"},{"type":"text","text":", and "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"pattern discovery"},{"type":"text","text":"."}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"In "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Generative AI"},{"type":"text","text":", unsupervised (and self-supervised) learning is used to "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"learn the data distribution"},{"type":"text","text":" and "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"generate new content"},{"type":"text","text":"."}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"The core difference from supervised learning is how the "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"objective function"},{"type":"text","text":" uses (or doesn use) labels."}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Unsupervised learning enables machines to "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"discover insights"},{"type":"text","text":" and "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"create new data"},{"type":"text","text":" without human-labeled training examples."}]}]}]},{"type":"paragraph"}]}}
